<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

  <meta
    name="description"
    content="Shepherd Guard provides cybersecurity monitoring, alert triage, and incident response guidance for churches. A part of Black Feather Security."
  />

  <title>Shepherd Guard | Security for Churches</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/styles.css" />

  <style>
    :root {
      --sg-gold: #d6a84f;
      --sg-gold-soft: rgba(214, 168, 79, 0.18);
    }

    .sg-gold {
      color: var(--sg-gold);
    }

    .sg-card {
      border: 1px solid rgba(214, 168, 79, 0.28);
    }

    .sg-hero-logo {
      max-width: 360px;
      width: 80%;
      margin: 0 auto 26px;
      display: block;
      filter: drop-shadow(0 0 24px rgba(214, 168, 79, 0.25));
    }

    .price {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin: 12px 0;
      color: #fff;
    }

    .price span {
      font-size: 1rem;
      opacity: 0.75;
      font-weight: 400;
    }

    .recommended {
      border-color: rgba(214, 168, 79, 0.65);
      box-shadow: 0 0 35px rgba(214, 168, 79, 0.12);
    }

    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      padding: 5px 10px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(214, 168, 79, 0.45);
      color: var(--sg-gold);
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      border-radius: 999px;
    }

    .mini-note {
      margin-top: 16px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      opacity: 0.75;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="wrap">

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <header class="header">
      <div class="brand">
        <img src="assets/images/shepherd-guard-logo.png" alt="Shepherd Guard" class="logo" />
        <div class="brand-text">
          <div class="name">Shepherd Guard</div>
          <div class="tag">Security for Churches</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="index.html">Black Feather Security</a>
        <a href="#services">Services</a>
        <a href="#pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="snapshot.html">Free Snapshot</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <img
          src="assets/images/shepherd-guard-logo-full.png"
          alt="Shepherd Guard - Security for Churches"
          class="sg-hero-logo"
        />

        <p class="eyebrow">A part of Black Feather Security</p>

        <h1>
          Protect Your Church Without Needing a Security Team
        </h1>

        <p class="sub">
          Shepherd Guard provides church-focused cybersecurity monitoring, alert triage,
          and incident response guidance for ministries that need protection,
          clarity, and support without enterprise-level complexity.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href="mailto:security@blackfeathersecurity.com?subject=Free Church Security Snapshot">
            Get a Free Church Security Snapshot
          </a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="#pricing">
            View Pricing
          </a>
        </div>

        <p style="margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.9rem; opacity: 0.8;">
          Built for churches, ministries, staff, volunteers, and leadership teams
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- TRUST STATEMENT -->
      <section class="card statement sg-card">
        <h2>Most Churches Carry Real Risk—and Limited Security Support</h2>
        <p>
          Churches manage member data, giving platforms, staff accounts, email systems,
          volunteer access, and sensitive communications. Attackers often target these
          environments through phishing, compromised accounts, exposed data, and unauthorized logins.
          Shepherd Guard helps you see what matters before it becomes a crisis.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- SERVICES -->
      <section id="services" class="section">
        <h2>Security That Fits a Church</h2>

        <div class="grid">

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>Monitoring</h3>
            <p>
              Ongoing visibility into suspicious activity, account risk, and warning signs
              that may affect your church.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>Alert Triage</h3>
            <p>
              We help separate meaningful alerts from noise so your leadership team is not
              left guessing.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>Incident Guidance</h3>
            <p>
              Clear next steps when something looks wrong, including practical response
              recommendations.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>Email & Account Risk</h3>
            <p>
              Focused attention on compromised accounts, suspicious logins, phishing,
              and access misuse.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>External Security Snapshot</h3>
            <p>
              A practical review of what is visible from the outside before attackers use it.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>Leadership Reporting</h3>
            <p>
              Simple monthly summaries written for decision-makers, not security engineers.
            </p>
          </article>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- PROCESS -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>

        <div class="steps">

          <article class="card step sg-card">
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Review</h3>
            <p>We identify your current tools, accounts, access risks, and public exposure.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card step sg-card">
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Monitor</h3>
            <p>We watch for suspicious behavior and indicators that may require action.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card step sg-card">
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Alert</h3>
            <p>You receive clear guidance when something matters—not confusing noise.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card step sg-card">
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>Respond</h3>
            <p>We help your team understand what happened and what to do next.</p>
          </article>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- PRICING -->
      <section id="pricing" class="section">
        <h2>Church-Friendly Pricing</h2>

        <div class="grid">

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>Starter</h3>
            <p>Awareness for small churches.</p>

            <div class="price">$99<span>/month</span></div>

            <p>
              Includes quarterly external security snapshot, basic alert monitoring,
              email notifications, and monthly summary reporting.
            </p>

            <p class="mini-note">
              Best for small congregations or churches with minimal IT support.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card sg-card recommended">
            <div class="badge">Recommended</div>
            <h3>Standard</h3>
            <p>Practical protection for growing churches.</p>

            <div class="price">$249<span>/month</span></div>

            <p>
              Includes continuous monitoring, alert triage, suspicious login detection,
              monthly reporting, and incident response guidance.
            </p>

            <p class="mini-note">
              Best for churches with staff, online giving, and multiple systems.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card sg-card">
            <h3>Guardian</h3>
            <p>Higher-confidence support for larger ministries.</p>

            <div class="price">$499<span>/month</span></div>

            <p>
              Includes everything in Standard, priority alerting, incident investigation
              support, detection tuning, and quarterly security review calls.
            </p>

            <p class="mini-note">
              Best for larger churches, multi-campus churches, and higher-risk environments.
            </p>
          </article>

        </div>

        <section class="card statement sg-card" style="margin-top: 30px;">
          <h2>Optional One-Time Assessment</h2>
          <p>
            <span class="sg-gold"><strong>Church Security Assessment — $299.</strong></span>
            A focused review of exposure, access risk, and practical recommendations your team can act on.
          </p>
        </section>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA BLOCK -->
      <section id="contact" class="card contact sg-card">
        <h2>Start With a Free Church Security Snapshot</h2>

        <p>
          Begin with a free external review. No intrusive testing, no disruption,
          and no technical pressure—just a clear look at what may be visible to attackers.
        </p>

        <a class="button primary" href="mailto:security@blackfeathersecurity.com?subject=Free Church Security Snapshot">
          Request Your Free Church Security Snapshot
        </a>

        <p style="margin-top: 15px;">
          Or email:
          <a href="mailto:security@blackfeathersecurity.com">
            security@blackfeathersecurity.com
          </a>
        </p>

        <p style="margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; opacity: 0.7;">
          Shepherd Guard is a part of Black Feather Security.
        </p>
      </section>

    </main>

    <!-- FOOTER -->
    <footer class="footer">
      <div>© <span id="year"></span> Shepherd Guard</div>

      <div class="legal">
        Security for Churches | A part of Black Feather Security
      </div>
    </footer>

  </div>

  <script>
    document.getElementById("year").textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
